<doc id="932799" wikidata="Q148047" url="?curid=932799" title="Dominica at the 2004 Summer Olympics">
<text>Dominica competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece, from 13 to 29 August 2004. The country&#x27;s participation at Athens marked its third appearance in the Summer Olympics since its debut in the 1996 Summer Olympics. Two track and field athletes, Chris Lloyd and Marie-Lyne Joseph were selected to represent the nation, the latter by a wildcard place as the nation had no other athletes that met either the &quot;A&quot; or &quot;B&quot; qualifying standards apart from Lloyd. Lloyd was selected as flag bearer for the opening ceremony.

==Athletics ==

Dominican athletes have so far achieved qualifying standards in the following athletics events (up to a maximum of 3 athletes in each event at the &#x27;A&#x27; Standard, and 1 at the &#x27;B&#x27; Standard).

;Men
;Women
