<doc id="932903" wikidata="Q5325035" url="?curid=932903" title="Eagle Butte, Alberta">
<text>Eagle Butte is a rural area south of Medicine Hat and west of the Cypress Hills. It is home to Saint Margaret&#x27;s Church. Formerly there was a NWMP post in the area. The first post office opened in 1900. The locality takes its name from a nearby butte of the same name. It is near the location of a confirmed impact crater 10 km in diameter at 49°42&#x27;N110°31&#x27;W around 65 million years ago.

==References==</text><links>
